Practical No. 5: Configuring a Zone-Based Policy Firewall
Aim: 
Configuring a Zone-Based Policy Firewall (ZPF)

steps:

Step 1: Verify Connectivity

Open Cisco Packet Tracer.

Configure IP addresses on PCs and router interfaces.

Test connectivity using ping.

PC> ping 192.168.1.1

Step 2: Create Security Zones

Router> enable
Router# configure terminal
Router(config)# zone security INSIDE
Router(config)# zone security OUTSIDE

Step 3: Assign Interfaces to Zones

Router(config)# interface g0/0
Router(config-if)# zone-member security INSIDE
Router(config-if)# exit

Router(config)# interface g0/1
Router(config-if)# zone-member security OUTSIDE
Router(config-if)# exit

Step 4: Create Class Map

Router(config)# class-map type inspect match-any CLASS1
Router(config-cmap)# match protocol http
Router(config-cmap)# match protocol https
Router(config-cmap)# exit

Step 5: Create Policy Map

Router(config)# policy-map type inspect POLICY1
Router(config-pmap)# class type inspect CLASS1
Router(config-pmap-c)# inspect
Router(config-pmap)# exit

Step 6: Create Zone Pair

Router(config)# zone-pair security ZP1 source INSIDE destination OUTSIDE
Router(config-sec-zone-pair)# service-policy type inspect POLICY1

Step 7: Verify Configuration

Router# show zone security
Router# show policy-map type inspect
Router# show zone-pair security
